The problem deals with graph theory and parameterized complexity, suggesting that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of degenerate graphs and the study of tracking sets also suggest categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of a kernel and the analysis of the problem's complexity suggest a connection to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
